  1→//! Three-stage cascade router for model selection (section 13.8-13.11).
  2→//!
  3→//! The cascade combines three routing strategies, automatically transitioning
  4→//! as observation count grows:
  5→//!
  6→//! | Stage | Name | Observations | Strategy |
  7→//! |-------|------|-------------|----------|
  8→//! | 1 | Static | < 50 | Hardcoded role -> model table |
  9→//! | 2 | Confidence | 50 - 200 | Empirical pass rates + confidence interval |
 10→//! | 3 | UCB1 | > 200 | Full `LinUCB` contextual bandit |
 11→//!
 12→//! # [`CascadeModel`]
 13→//!
 14→//! The router returns a [`CascadeModel`] containing a primary model,
 15→//! an ordered fallback chain, an optional context-overflow fallback,
 16→//! and a latency SLA in milliseconds.
 17→//!
 18→//! # Thread safety
 19→//!
 20→//! The cascade wraps a [`LinUCBRouter`] and an additional
 21→//! [`parking_lot::Mutex`] for confidence-stage statistics.
 22→
